result.execSummary:
The defendant Eligio R Bacallao Jr was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. On one or more other charges, Eligio R Bacallao Jr was found not guilty. These charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Eligio R Bacallao Jr is presumed innocent of the not guilty charges.

  • Eligio R Bacallao Jr was found guilty of Stalking - Result in Bodily Harm [Modifiers: Repeater], a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.32(2).
  • Eligio R Bacallao Jr was found guilty of Threats to Injure/Accuse of Crime [Modifiers: Repeater], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.30(1).
  • Eligio R Bacallao Jr was found guilty of Bail Jumping-Felony [Modifiers: Repeater], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).
  • Eligio R Bacallao Jr was found guilty of Bail Jumping-Felony [Modifiers: Repeater], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).
  • Eligio R Bacallao Jr was found guilty of Strangulation and Suffocation [Modifiers: Repeater], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.235(1).
  • Eligio R Bacallao Jr was found guilty of Bail Jumping-Felony [Modifiers: Repeater], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).
  • Eligio R Bacallao Jr was found guilty of 3rd Degree Sexual Assault, a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.225(3).
  • Eligio R Bacallao Jr was found guilty of Bail Jumping-Felony [Modifiers: Repeater], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).

Reporter: Heather Kieta
Defendant appeared in court and requested Court appoint counsel and that he be allowed to proceed with a trial to a jury; Atty Mimier objected arguing that Defendant had waived his right to both; Court made record of previous collequies with Defendant about his rights to and the advantages of having counsel, his waiver of a jury trial and previous findings that Defendant was competent to proceed; Court affirmed that Defendant's previous waivers of right to counsel and the right to a jury trial had been made knowingly, intelligently and voluntarily and denied Defendant's requests; Defendant advised he no longer wished to participate in the court proceedings and that he be removed from the courtroom; the Court advised the Defendant of the rights he would be giving up if he failed to participate and gave him the options of appearing by video or telephone conference; the Defendant refused to participate in any court proceedings and was returned to the jail; the Court did make contact with the Defendant in the jail, at which time he advised he would appear by video conference but when arrangements were being made, he again refused to participate; Court found Defendant voluntarily gave up his right to participate and proceeded with trial; State's evidence continued - testimony and exhibits; State rested; Court found there was sufficient evidence for a fact finder to make a determination of guilt or innocence of the charged offense(s) and if any constructive motion for dismissal had been made it would be denied; Court recessed and when it reconvened, Defendant advised he would participate and be present in the courtroom to present evidence; Defendant's evidence - testimony taken; Defendant rested; State presented no rebuttal evidence; Court adjourned and took case under advisement to deliberate on its verdict

Reporter: Linda Flakne
Court provided Atty Mimier and the Defendant a copy of the jury instructions to assist them with argument at the close of evidence; State's case continued - testimony and exhibits; Defendant requested Court adjourn for the day due to his inability to proceed because of the side effects of medication that he was administered and further requested the Court to appoint him counsel; Court made record regarding Defendant's clear understanding of his right to counsel having had numerous colloquies with the Defendant at prior hearings and each time waiving his right to counsel; Court also made a record as to the two previous competency evaluations that were performed and the findings each time that the Defendant was competent to stand trial; Court denied Defendant's request for counsel and adjourned and advised it would reconvene on 10-30-2014
